Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @Pak Choi{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced widthways).

Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} and onion to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the chicken has browned all over and the veg is starting to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lower the heat to medium, then add the sliced pak choi and @Ginger Puree{15%g} to the chicken and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Miso Paste{22%g}, @Hoisin Sauce{32%g}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and @Water for the Sauce{75%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then simmer gently until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When everything's ready, share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the Beijing style chicken.

Enjoy!